        public static Integer toInteger​(String strNum)
        Convert to Integer.

        This class allow to convert a String to an Integer, returning zero if the conversion fails. 

           StringNumberUtils.toInteger( "" ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.toDouble( "A" ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.toInteger( null ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.toInteger( "123" ) = 123;
        Parameters:
        strNum - String to convert.
        Returns:
        Integer value that represented by String value or zero if conversition fail.

      • compare

        public static int compare​(String strNum1,
                          String strNum2)
        Compare two String.

        This method compares two version string as input and returns whether one is greater than, equal, or less than the other.

        This method uses Locale.getDefault() from Java Virtual Machine to specific geographic, cultural, or political region. 

           StringNumberUtils.compare( "", "" ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "strNum1", "strNum2" ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( null, null ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "1.2", "1.1" ) = 1;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "1.1", "1.1" ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "1.1", "1.2" ) = -1;
        Parameters:
        strNum1 - First String to evaluate.
        strNum2 - Second String to evaluate.
        Returns:
        the value 0 if strNum1 == strNum2; a value -1 if strNum1 < strNum2; and a value 1 if strNum1 > strNum2;

      • compare

        public static int compare​(String strNum1,
                          String strNum2,
                          Locale locale)
        Compare two String.

        This method compares two version string as input and returns whether one is greater than, equal, or less than the other. 

           StringNumberUtils.compare( "", "", Locale.CANADA ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "strNum1", "strNum2", Locale.CANADA ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( null, null, Locale.CANADA ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "1.2", "1.1", Locale.CANADA ) = 1;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "1.1", "1.1", Locale.CANADA ) = 0;
   StringNumberUtils.compare( "1.1", "1.2", Locale.CANADA ) = -1;
        Parameters:
        strNum1 - First String to evaluate.
        strNum2 - Second String to evaluate.
        locale - Locale object represents a specific geographic, cultural, or political region.
        Returns:
        the value 0 if strNum1 == strNum2; a value -1 if strNum1 < strNum2; and a value 1 if strNum1 > strNum2;
